title: Independent candidate Nisar Ahmed wins NA-100 seat
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Independent candidate Nisar Ahmed has won the election for National Assembly constituency NA-100 Faisalabad VI by securing 131,941 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Rana Sanaullah Khan of Pakistan Muslim League-Nawaz (PML-N) who bagged 112,639 votes.
Overall votersâ€™ turn-out remained 55.25 per cent.
